For the receiving of LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrPasswordRecoveryState.name: swL2DevCtrPasswordRecoveryState

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency.description: Indicates the maximum amount of time the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit packets before allowing the next lowest priority queue to begin transmitting its packets. A value between 0 and 255 can be specified- with this value multiplied by 16 ms to arrive at the total allowed time for queue to transmit packets. For example, a value of 3 specifies 3*16=48 ms. The queue will continue transmitting the last packet until it is finished when the max_latency timer expires.

swL2IpMacBindingPortDHCPSnoopMaxEntry.description: This object indicates the max entry created by DHCP packets on the specified port. Note: When 0 is set on the specified port, the max entry created by DHCP packets is no limit

swL2IpMacBindingPortDHCPSnoopEntryClearA.name: swL2IpMacBindingPortDHCPSnoopEntryClearAction
swL2IpMacBindingPortDHCPSnoopEntryClearA.description: When set to start (2), the address binding entries learned for the specified ports will be cleared. When get, it always returns other (1).

swL2IpMacBindingPortStopLearningThreshol.name: swL2IpMacBindingPortStopLearningThreshold
swL2IpMacBindingPortStopLearningThreshol.description: This object indicates the threshold to stop learning new MAC addresses on the specified port. When the number of blocked entries exceeds the threshold, the port will stop learning new addresses. The packet with a new address will be dropped. Note: When 0 is set on the specified port, it means no limit.

swL2IpMacBindingEntry.name: swL2IpMacBindingEntry

swL2IpMacBindingIpIndex.name: swL2IpMacBindingIpIndex
swL2IpMacBindingIpIndex.description: The IP address of the IP-MAC binding.

swL2IpMacBindingMac.name: swL2IpMacBindingMac
swL2IpMacBindingMac.description: The MAC address of the IP-MAC binding.

swL2IpMacBindingPorts.name: swL2IpMacBindingPorts
swL2IpMacBindingPorts.description: The port members of this entry.

swL2IpMacBindingMode.name: swL2IpMacBindingMode
swL2IpMacBindingMode.description: The mode of this entry. arp: This entry is specified as an ARP mode entry, and this entry will not be added as an access entry. If this object is not specified, the mode defaults to ARP mode. If the system is in ARP mode, the ARP mode entries and ACL mode entries will be effective. If the system is in ACL mode, only the ACL mode entries will be active. acl: This entry is specified as an ACL mode entry. If the user enables the ACL mode, this entry will be added as an access entry. auto: This mode cannot be configured, and when the auto mode is employed, it means this entry is to be learned by DHCP snooping.

swL2IpMacBindingBlockedTable.name: swL2IpMacBindingBlockedTable
swL2IpMacBindingBlockedTable.description: The table specifies information of MAC addresses which were blocked.

swL2IpMacBindingBlockedMac.name: swL2IpMacBindingBlockedMac

swL2IpMacBindingBlockedVlanName.name: swL2IpMacBindingBlockedVlanName
swL2IpMacBindingBlockedVlanName.description: This object specifies the VLAN name.

swL2IpMacBindingBlockedPort.name: swL2IpMacBindingBlockedPort

swL2IpMacBindingBlockedType.name: swL2IpMacBindingBlockedType
swL2IpMacBindingBlockedType.description: The value is always blockByAddrBind. This entry will be deleted by setting the value to delete(3).

swL2IpMacBindingAllPortState.name: swL2IpMacBindingAllPortState
swL2IpMacBindingAllPortState.description: This object enables/disables IP-MAC binding on all ports of the system. This action is only applicable when users have write privileges, and can only be viewed when users have read privileges. Note: enable-strict (2): This means strict mode (SW learning). All packets are sent to the CPU. If the user chooses, the port will check ARP packets and IP packets by IP-MAC-PORT Binding entries. If the MAC address can be found or not found by the entry, the MAC will be set as dynamic learned or it will set as blocked, respectively. Other packets will be sent to the CPU and dropped. enable-loose (4) : This means loose mode (HW learning): Only ARP packets and IP broadcast packets will be sent to the CPU. If the user chooses , the port will learn the MAC address on non-ARP and non-IP broadcast packets directly, so these packets will be bypassed. But if the switch receives the ARP or IP broadcast packets and Can not bypass the IP MAC Binding checking, the switch will set this MAC address as blocked and all packets from this MAC address will be dropped.

swL2IpMacBindingTrapLogState.name: swL2IpMacBindingTrapLogState
swL2IpMacBindingTrapLogState.description: when set to enable(2),whenever there's a new MAC that violates the pre-defined Ip Mac Binding configuration, the trap will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged into the system.

swL2IpMacBindingARPInspectionState.name: swL2IpMacBindingARPInspectionState
swL2IpMacBindingARPInspectionState.description: Used to set ARP inspection state.

swL2IpMacBindingACLMode.name: swL2IpMacBindingACLMode
swL2IpMacBindingACLMode.description: when set to enable(2), the Ip Mac Binding will use acl mode

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopState.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopState
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopState.description: When the dhcp_snoop function is enabled, all address_binding disabled ports will act as DHCP server ports (the switch will learn IP addresses through DHCP server ports (by DHCP OFFER and DHCP ACK packets)). The auto-learned IP-MAC binding entry will be mapped to a specific source port based on the MAC address learning function. This entry will be created as an ACL-mode binding entry for this specific port. Each entry is associated with a lease time. When the lease time expires, the expired entry will be removed from this port. The automatically learned binding entry can be moved from one port to another port if the DHCP snooping function has learned that the MAC address has moved to a different port. Consider a case where DHCP snooping learns a binding entry, and the same IP-MAC binding entry has been statically configured. Suppose that the learned information is consistent with the statically configured entry, then the automatically learned entry will not be created. Suppose the entry is statically configured in ARP mode, since the automatically learned entry will be created in ACL mode, the entry will become ACL mode. Suppose the entry is statically configured on one port and the entry is automatically learned on another port, then both entries will exist. When the dhcp_snoop function is disabled, all of the automatically learned binding entries will be removed.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntryClearAllSt.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntryClearAllState
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntryClearAllSt.description: Used to clear all entries created by DHCP packets.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopTable.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopTable
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopTable.description: The table specifies information regarding the DHCP snooping function learning IP-MAC binding entries.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntry.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntry
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopEntry.description: A list of information about the DHCP snooping learning IP-MAC binding entry.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopIpIndex.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopIpIndex
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopIpIndex.description: The IP address of this entry.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopMac.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopMac
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopMac.description: The MAC address of this entry.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopLeaseTime.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopLeaseTime
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopLeaseTime.description: Specifies the lease time of this entry. When the lease time expires, this entry will be removed from this port.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopPort.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopPort
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopPort.description: Specifies the port of this entry.

swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopStatus.name: swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopStatus
swL2IpMacBindingDHCPSnoopStatus.description: Specifies the status (inactive or active) of this entry.

swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEntry.name: swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEntry
swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEntry.description: A list of information of each permitted IP pool entry.

swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStartIP.name: swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStartIP
swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStartIP.description: The start IP address of the permitted IP pool.

swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEndIP.name: swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEndIP
swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolEndIP.description: The end IP address of the permitted IP pool.

swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolPorts.name: swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolPorts
swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolPorts.description: The port members of the permitted IP pool.

swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStatus.name: swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStatus
swL2IpMacBindingPermitIPPoolStatus.description: The status of the permitted IP pool.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current active number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifies which ports are grouped as a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies which ports are grouped as a set of ports(up to 8) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk. The trunk group number depends on the existence of the unit and module.

swL2TrunkName.name: swL2TrunkName
swL2TrunkName.description: The name of logical port trunk.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be the same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicates how many ports are included in this Trunk. The trunk port number depends on the existence of module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunks.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of the trunk group. static : is static trunk group lacp : is LACP trunk group .

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures the part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates which port will sniff another port to the switch. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: This represents the ingress of the source port packet to be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: This represents the egress of the source port packet to be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different for each of the following values. disabled(2) - writing this value to the object will remove the corresponding entry from the table. enabled(3) - this entry will reside in the table.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of VLANs in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: This table controls the VLAN's IGMP function. Its scale depends on the current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If VLAN is in disabled mode, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with an index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN ID. If VLAN is disabled, the VID is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Base mode, the VID is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the VID setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the Vid in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which the IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to have a high loss, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packet when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works in per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer has expired. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a query receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decides if the IGMP query is enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different for each of the following values. disable(2) - IGMP funtion is disabled for this entry. enable(3) - IGMP funtion is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the current number of IGMP query packets which have been captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entires are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of the IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function has been enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, on a per-VLAN basis. In case of the IGMP timer expiration, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increments this object by 1.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which have been captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entries are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than the Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of the IGMP Table and the Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, the Filtering Table entry will overwrite the colliding entry of the IGMP Table. See swL2FilterMgmt description also.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entries are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the VID of individual IGMP table entries. It shows the VID of IGMP report information captured on the network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object identifies group ip address which have been captured from the IGMP packet, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object identifies mac addresses which correspond to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports belong to the same multicast group, on a per-Vlan basis. Each multicast group has a octect string to indicate with port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets represent one unit port according to its logic port. If the unit has less then 32 port, the other ports don't care and just fill in zero.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicates how many report packets were received by the device corresponding with this entry where the IGMP function is enabled, on a per-Vlan basis.

swL2IGMPGroupActive.name: swL2IGMPGroupActive
swL2IGMPGroupActive.description: This object indicates that the entry added the multicast table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.description: The information of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN id of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.description: This object indicates the portlist of the source ports of IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as tag ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.description: This object indicates the portlist of the member ports of IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set to untag ports of the vlan entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports would be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIP.description: This object is used to replace the source IP address in the IP header for IGMP control packets.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.description: This indicates the untagged member ports to add to the multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.description: This is the priority value (0 to 7) to be associated with the data traffic to be forwarded on the multicast VLAN. When set to -1, the packet's original priority will be used.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.description: This specifies that a packet's priority will be changed by the switch based on the remap priority. This flag will only take effect when remap priority is set.

swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.description: The information of the router port table.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN id of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.description: This object indicates the static portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.description: This object indicates the dynamic portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.description: This object indicates the forbidden portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable
swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP Access Authentication configurations of the device.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry
swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP Access Authentication. The configuration is done per port.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort
swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.description: The index of the swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable. This object corresponds to the port being configured.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthState
swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.description: This object denotes the status of IGMP Access Authentication of the port.

swL2DhcpRelayState.name: swL2DhcpRelayState
swL2DhcpRelayState.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.name: swL2DhcpRelayHopCount
swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that the DHCP packets can cross.

swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.name: swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold
swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the DHCP packet.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82State
swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay agent information option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.description: This object indicates if the checking mechanism of DHCP relay agent information option 82 is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.description: This object indicates the re-forwarding policy is DHCP relay agent information option 82. replace(1) - replace the exiting option 82 field in messages. drop(2) - discard messages with existing option 82 field. keep(3) - retain the existing option 82 field in messages.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.description: This table specifies the IP address og the destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifying the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object, results in the corresponding entry being removed from the table. valid(3) - this entry will reside in the table.

swL2LoopDetectAdminState.name: swL2LoopDetectAdminState
swL2LoopDetectAdminState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection status of the system.

swL2LoopDetectInterval.name: swL2LoopDetectInterval
swL2LoopDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the interval value, the range is from 1 to 32767 seconds.

swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.name: swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime
swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.description: This object indicates the recover time, the range is from 60 to 1000000. A value of 0 disables the recover function.

swL2LoopDetectMode.name: swL2LoopDetectMode
swL2LoopDetectMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList1to64.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList1to64
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList1to64.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1-512) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList65to128.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList65to128
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList65to128.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (513-1024) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList129to19.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList129to192
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList129to19.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1025-1536) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList193to25.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList193to256
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList193to25.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (1537-2048) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList257to32.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList257to320
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList257to32.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2049-2560) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList321to38.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList321to384
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList321to38.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (2561-3072) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList385to44.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList385to448
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList385to44.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3073-3584) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList449to51.name: swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList449to512
swL2LoopDetectActiveVlanRangeList449to51.description: This object indicates the VLAN range (3585-4096) that added the multicast table.

swL2LoopDetectPortTable.name: swL2LoopDetectPortTable
swL2LoopDetectPortTable.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by the port.

swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.name: swL2LoopDetectPortEntry
swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by the port.

swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.name: swL2LoopDetectPortIndex
swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number. The range is from 1 to the maximum port number specified in the module

swL2LoopDetectPortState.name: swL2LoopDetectPortState
swL2LoopDetectPortState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection function state on the port.

swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN.name: swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN
swL2LoopDetectPortLoopVLAN.description: This object indicates the VLAN list that has detected a loopback.

swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.name: swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus
swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.description: This object indicates the port status.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifies that the port can just forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information specifying the port with its traffic forward list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can forward traffic to.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: port security feature which controls the address learning capability and the traffic forwarding decision. Each port can have this function enabled or disabled. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned at this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as static entry. When the learned addresses number reaches N, any incoming packet that has not learned a source addresses is discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates the secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses to be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout(3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after aging timer has expired. In this mode, when the locked address has aged out, the number of addresses that can be learned has to increase by one. In deleteOnReset(4) mode - never age out the locked addresses unless restarting the system to prevent from port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates the administration state of the locking address.

swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.name: swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState
swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.description: when enable(2)is selected,whenever there's a new MAC that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, a trap will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged in system.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP local relay function of the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the DHCP local relay status for each VLAN.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.description: This object lists the current VLANs in the switch and their corresponding DHCP local relay status.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.description: This object shows the VIDs of the current VLANS in the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP relay function of the VLAN.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Table.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Table
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Table.description: This table is used to manage the DHCP local relay option 82 policy for each port.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Entry.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Entry
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Entry.description: This object lists the current ports in the switch and their corresponding DHCP local relay option 82 policy.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82PortIndex.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82PortIndex
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82PortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Policy.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Policy
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82Policy.description: This object indicates the policy of the DHCP local relay option 82 of each port.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteIDType.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteIDType
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteIDType.description: This object indicates the type of remote ID for DHCP Local Relay. If the type is default, the remote ID will be the MAC address of the device. If the type is user-defined, the remote ID can be defined by writing to the swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteID object.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteID.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteID
swL2DhcpLocalRelayOption82RemoteID.description: This object displays the current remote ID of the device for DHCP Local Relay. If swL2DhcpRelayOption82RemoteIDType is set to default, the value will be the MAC address of the device, and this object cannot be modified. If swL2DhcpRelayOption82RemoteIDType is set to user-defined, a new value can be written to this object.

swL2PPPoECirIDinsertState.name: swL2PPPoECirIDinsertState
swL2PPPoECirIDinsertState.description: This object indicates the status of the PPPoE circuit ID insertion state of the switch.

swL2macNotification.name: swL2macNotification
swL2macNotification.description: This trap indicate the MAC addresses variation in the address table .

swL2porttypechgNotification.name: swL2porttypechgNotification
swL2porttypechgNotification.description: This trap indicates the port type change.

swPowerStatusChg.name: swPowerStatusChg
swPowerStatusChg.description: Power Status change notification. The notification is issued when the swPowerStatus changes as in the following cases: lowVoltage -> overCurrent. lowVoltage -> working. lowVoltage -> disconnect. lowVoltage -> connect. overCurrent -> lowVoltage. overCurrent -> working. overCurrent -> disconnect. overCurrent -> connect. working -> lowVoltage. working -> overCurrent. working -> connect. working -> disconnect. fail -> connect. fail -> disconnect. connect -> lowVoltage. connect -> overCurrent. connect -> working. connect -> disconnect. disconnect -> lowVoltage. disconnect -> overCurrent. disconnect -> working. disconnect -> connect.

swPowerFailure.name: swPowerFailure
